{{Quote|As you may know, the ''sacred circle'' is a religious order on our home planet, ''Monastery,'' we worship the eternal, ever-renewing circle of life.|Domina Tagge|<ref name="Star Wars (1977) 35">[[Star Wars (1977) 35|''Star Wars'' (1977) 35]]</ref>}}
The '''Order of the Sacred Circle''' was a religion that dominated the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Monastery/Legends|Monastery]]. The Order's name originated from the rings of debris circling the planet. The rings represented the eternal and ever-renewing cycle of life. The Order was ruled by a High Priestess and the main governing body was the Circle of Elders. Most of the time, the Order tried to remain neutral.

The Order already existed on the planet during the Old Republic era. Five-year-old [[Theron Shan]], son of [[Satele Shan]], a Jedi who later became the [[Grand Master/Legends|Grand Master]] of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]], spent six months as an acolyte of the Order, mastering the techniques of concentration.<ref name="Lost Suns 04">[[The Old Republic — The Lost Suns 4|''The Old Republic — The Lost Suns'' 4]]</ref> During the [[Separatist Crisis/Legends|Separatist Crisis]], Monastery opened up to refugees, provided that they converted to the Order upon their arrival.

During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], they stayed neutral due to their belief in the circle of life and that a war would break the circle and cause doom to the galaxy. [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] was dispatched by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] to convince the Order to side with the [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]]. Eventually, the leader of the Order, [[Domina Tagge/Legends|Domina Tagge]], was convinced to side with the Empire. Sister Domina had already planned to side with Vader to force him into dueling [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]. The Order suffered much from the Imperial presence on their home planet. When Domina stepped down as High Priestess of the Order, the Circle of Elders agreed to ally themselves with the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]].

